From b91c03875b9584e550bbf7cdde19ff5232aa42fa Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Anson Huang <b20788@freescale.com>
Date: Wed, 14 Aug 2013 11:26:46 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 0229/1072] ENGR00275023-1 ARM: imx: Enable unsafe resume for
 MMC

git://git.freescale.com/imx/linux-2.6-imx.git imx_3.10.17_1.0.0_beta
commit 3bfd822b8b9cbb7170cac212ab889aa05400d880

As we often use SD/MMC rootfs, need to enable this configuration
for successfully resume of rootfs, otherwise, rootfs will be
broken after resume.

Signed-off-by: Anson Huang <b20788@freescale.com>
Signed-off-by: Hongbo Zhong <hongbo.zhong@windriver.com>
---
 arch/arm/configs/imx_v6_v7_defconfig |    1 +
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm/configs/imx_v6_v7_defconfig b/arch/arm/configs/imx_v6_v7_defconfig
index e013bb3..9b5b874 100644
--- a/arch/arm/configs/imx_v6_v7_defconfig
+++ b/arch/arm/configs/imx_v6_v7_defconfig
@@ -221,6 +221,7 @@ CONFIG_USB_CHIPIDEA_HOST=y
 CONFIG_USB_PHY=y
 CONFIG_USB_MXS_PHY=y
 CONFIG_MMC=y
+CONFIG_MMC_UNSAFE_RESUME=y
 CONFIG_MMC_SDHCI=y
 CONFIG_MMC_SDHCI_PLTFM=y
 CONFIG_MMC_SDHCI_ESDHC_IMX=y
